[01:27.47]	Weigh you the worth and honour of a king
[01:30.87]	So great as our dread father in a scale
[01:34.20]	Of common ounces? will you with counters sum
[01:37.82]	The past proportion of his infinite?
[01:40.86]	And buckle in a waist most fathomless
[01:44.04]	With spans and inches so diminutive
[01:47.08]	As fears and reasons? fie, for godly shame!
[01:50.48]HELENUS	No marvel, though you bite so sharp at reasons,
[01:54.25]	You are so empty of them. Should not our father
[01:58.08]	Bear the great sway of his affairs with reasons,
[02:01.99]	Because your speech hath none that tells him so?
